{"article_id":"3o9V7vFpo0QshFod","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Despite a rapid succession of proposals and counteroffers between the White House and Capitol Hill in the past few days ,","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"House Speaker John Boehner today said","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"the two sides are nowhere near a deal on the `` fiscal cliff , ''","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"and continued to criticize what he called the president 's emphasis on tax revenue","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"instead of tackling the country 's long-term deficit problems .","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"`` The president 's plan","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"to avert the fiscal cliff","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"still does not meet the two standards","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"that I laid out the day after the election , ''","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"Boehner ,","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"R-Ohio ,","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"said .","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"`` His plan does not fulfill his promise","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"to bring a balanced approach","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"to solving this problem .","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"It 's mainly tax hikes ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"and his plan does not begin to solve our debt crisis .","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"It actually increases spending . ''","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"The speaker said","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"Obama proposed $ 1.4 trillion in new tax revenue ,","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"which is too high","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"to pass the House of Representatives ,","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"where a majority of members are still reluctant to increase taxes .","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"The two leaders spoke Tuesday evening on the phone","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"after the alternative offers moved up and down Pennsylvania Avenue , a conversation","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"the speaker described as `` deliberate . ''","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"`` That can not pass the House or the Senate , ''","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"Boehner said .","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"`` There were some offers","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"that were exchanged back and forth yesterday ,","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"and ,","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"you know ,","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"the president and I had a pretty frank conversation","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"about just how far apart we are , ''","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"Boehner said .","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"Boehner last week sent the president a pitch for $ 800 billion in new revenue ,","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"as long as the revenue was achieved through comprehensive tax overhaul","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"that closed loopholes and capped deductions , not changes to the tax rates .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"`` I was born with a glass half-full , ''","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"`` I remain the most optimistic person in this town ,","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"but we 've got some serious differences . ''","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"Asked whether it might take a day of steep losses in the financial markets to spook enough members into voting for an ultimate package ,","depth":5},{"id":43,"text":"Boehner declined to speculate .","depth":5},{"id":44,"text":"`` I 'm not going to talk about what outside factors could impact these negotiations ,","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"but I will say","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"that presidents get elected to lead , ''","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"`` We are going to begin to solve our debt problem ,","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"and we 're not going to be able to solve it","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"by kicking the can down the road","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"and doing all the gimmicks","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"that have been done in the past .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"It 's time","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"to address our spending problem . ''","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"President Obama predicted Monday","depth":5},{"id":56,"text":"that Republicans will ultimately accept tax hikes for the wealthy .","depth":5},{"id":57,"text":"`` Taxes are going up one way or another , ''","depth":6},{"id":58,"text":"the president told ABC 's Barbara Walters .","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"He said","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"Republicans should n't hold tax meausre for most Americans `` hostage ''","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"to protect the lower rates","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"that benefit top earners .","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"Republicans say","depth":4},{"id":64,"text":"allowing rates for the wealthy ,","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"many of whom are small business owners ,","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"to rise , will hurt the economy .","depth":5},{"id":67,"text":"Some lawmakers are tired of waiting for the negotiations between Boehner and the White House .","depth":3},{"id":68,"text":"Sen. Bob Corker , R-TN. , gave an impassioned speech on the issue today in the Senate .","depth":4},{"id":69,"text":"`` It looks like","depth":6},{"id":70,"text":"based on where the negotiations are right now","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"that this issue is going to move into next year , ''","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"he said .","depth":5},{"id":73,"text":"Corker is one of the few Republicans","depth":4},{"id":74,"text":"who has indicated in the past","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"that he would be open to higher tax rates for the wealthy","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"if lawmakers can try to pass a more sweeping tax reform package next year .","depth":5},{"id":77,"text":"`` We can put our head in the sand","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"but we know","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"we 're going to deal with a portion of the revenue issue at year end , ''","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"Corker said ,","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"`` what I would say to my friends in the house is that candidly ,","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"if we are able to rescue the 98 %","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"and then we dealt with the upper 2 % either with rates or by tax deductions","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"- I 'm open to both -","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"and we even protected the small businesses","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"like so many people on sides of the aisle have suggested . ''","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"In an attempt","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"to not just wait for a deal ,","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"Corker says","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"he 'll propose a deal of his own in the next day","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"that will would cut , reform Medicare , Social Security , and Medicaid by $ 900 billion to $ 1 trillion","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"and offer a suggestion","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"for raising the debt ceiling by $ 900 billion to $ 1 trillion .","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"`` At the end of this year , in some form or fashion","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"whether we embarrass ourselves","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"and go over the cliff","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"or before this year ends ,","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"we 're going to offer revenues , right ?","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"I do n't know","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"how anybody could believe that revenues are n't coming","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"so would I would say to everyone here ,","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"let 's move to entitlement reform . ''","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":205,"left":169,"right":204,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":169,"left":157,"right":168,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":144,"right":156,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":137,"right":143,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":120,"right":136,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":107,"right":119,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":107,"left":0,"right":106,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":106,"left":104,"right":105,"relation"